# React Component Conventions

Apply this rule to reusable React components in this repo.

- Define props as `interface <ComponentName>Props`.
- Export reusable components as named `const` values.
- Prefer `React.FC<Props>` for reusable components.
- Prefer one component per file.
- Do not use default exports for reusable components.

Preferred pattern:

```tsx
interface MyComponentProps {
  prop1: string;
}

export const MyComponent: React.FC<MyComponentProps> = ({ prop1 }) => {
  return <div>{prop1}</div>;
};
```

Do not force this pattern onto framework files that require special exports, including `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `template.tsx`, `default.tsx`, and route handlers.
